9 1, 2026]. Sec. 34. (a) When a vacancy occurs in the superior court of
10 Lake County, the clerk of the court shall promptly notify the
11 chairperson and each member of the commission of the vacancy. The
12 chairperson shall call a meeting of the commission within ten (10) days
13 following the notice. The commission shall submit its nominations of
14 five (5) candidates for each vacancy and certify them to the governor
15 as promptly as possible, and not later than sixty (60) days after the
16 vacancy occurs. When it is known that a vacancy will occur at a
17 definite future date within the term of the governor then serving, but
18 the vacancy has not yet occurred, the clerk shall notify the chairperson
19 and each member of the commission immediately of the forthcoming
20 vacancy, and the commission may within fifty (50) days of the notice
21 of the vacancy make its nominations and submit to the governor the
22 names of five (5) persons nominated for the forthcoming vacancy.
23 (b) Meetings of the commission shall be called by its chairperson or,
24 if the chairperson fails to call a necessary meeting, upon the call of any
25 four (4) members of the commission. The chairperson, whenever the
26 chairperson considers a meeting necessary, or upon the request by any
27 four (4) members of the commission for a meeting, shall give each
28 member of the commission at least five (5) days written notice by mail
29 of the date, time, and place of every meeting unless the commission at
30 its previous meeting designated the date, time, and place of its next
31 meeting.
32 (c) Meetings of the commission are to be held at the Lake County
33 government center in Crown Point or another place, as the circuit court
34 clerk of Lake County may arrange, at the direction of the chairperson
35 of the commission.
36 (d) The commission may act only at a public meeting. IC 5-14-1.5
37 applies to meetings of the commission. The commission may not meet
38 in executive session under IC 5-14-1.5-6.1 for the consideration of a
39 candidate for judicial appointment.
40 (e) The commission may act only by the concurrence of a majority
41 of its voting members attending a meeting. Four (4) voting members
42 constitute a quorum at a meeting.
